-- Ukraine’s Energoatom Gets $80 Million Loan, Kommersant Says
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-03-01T07:06:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/ukraine-s-energoatom-gets-80-million-loan-kommersant-says.html
Ukraine’s state-run nuclear-plant
operator, DP NAEK Energoatom, got an $80 million one-year loan
from state lender Export-Import Bank, Kommersant-Ukraine
reported, citing documents it obtained.  The loan has a 13 percent annual interest rate, according
to the Kiev-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
